An introduction and some prospectives are provided for the 1971 ACM Information Storage and Retrieval Symposium held at the University of Maryland on April 1 and 2, 1971. The symposium, sponsored by the University of Maryland, the National Aeronautics and Space Administration and the Special Interest Group on Information Retrieval (SIGIR) of the ACM, focuses on advances in techniques in the computer oriented technology of information retrieval. Early developments and the status of recent efforts in document retrieval, quesiton-answering and data management systems are reviewed briefly.